[[File:Charles Alluaud (1861-1949).png|right|thumb|<center>Charles A. Alluaud]]
'''Charles A. Alluaud''' (4 May 1861, [[Limoges]] – 12 December 1949, [[Crozant]]) was a [[France|French]] [[entomologist]].

The Alluaud family had owned porcelain factories since the 18th century. His great grandfather had been chairman of the ''{{lang|fr|[[Ancienne Manufacture Royale de Limoges]]}}'' and his grandfather, [[François Alluaud]] (1778–1866), was a  porcelain manufacturer, archaeologist, and [[geologist]]. [[Jean-Baptiste-Camille Corot]] (1796–1875) taught painting to Charles and his brother Eugene.

Charles left Limoges for Paris to supplement his studies but was an undisciplined pupil. The death of his parents enabled him to become an explorer. From 1887 to 1930, he went on many journeys in [[Africa]] ([[Ivory Coast]], [[Madagascar]], [[Kilimanjaro]], [[Tunisia]], [[Morocco]], [[Sudan]], the [[Sahara]], [[Niger]]), the [[Canary Islands]], [[Seychelles]] and [[Mascarene Islands]]. He assembled an important collections of insects during his voyages, later giving these to the entomology department of the ''{{lang|fr|[[Muséum national d'histoire naturelle]]}}''. He was the author of 165 entomological publications. He was president of the ''{{lang|fr|[[Société entomologique de France]]}}'' in 1899 and 1914.{{Citation needed|date=October 2017}} 

==Legacy==
[[Emmanuel Drake del Castillo]] (1855–1904) dedicated the plant [[genus]] ''[[Alluaudia]]'' to him.{{Citation needed|date=October 2017}}

A genus and three [[species]] of reptiles are named in his honor: ''[[Alluaudina]]'', ''[[Amphiglossus|Amphiglossos alluaudi]]'', ''[[Langaha|Langaha alluaudi]]'', and ''[[Uroplatus|Uroplatus alluaudi]]''.<ref>Beolens, Bo; Watkins, Michael; Grayson, Michael (2011). ''The Eponym Dictionary of Reptiles''. Baltimore: Johns Hopkins University Press. xiii + 296 pp. {{ISBN|978-1-4214-0135-5}}. ("Alluaud", p. 6).</ref> A species of ant, ''[[Plagiolepis alluaudi]]'', is also named after him.<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Wetterer |first=James K |date=2013 |title=Worldwide spread of Alluaud's little yellow ant, Plagiolepis alluaudi (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/James_Wetterer/publication/257645062_Worldwide_spread_of_Alluaud's_little_yellow_ant_Plagiolepis_alluaudi_Hymenoptera_Formicidae/links/004635258d701ef3aa000000.pdf |journal=Myrmecol. News |volume=19 |pages=53–59 |issn=1994 -4136 |via=ResearchGate |access-date=2017-11-16}}</ref>

